---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Kitchen Pantry Tiling ‚Äî TILERSHUB Sri Lanka"
  description="Professional kitchen countertop and backsplash tiling in Sri Lanka. Rs. 5,000 per linear foot, waterproof joints, perfect alignment. TILERSHUB."
  eyebrow="Kitchen Pantry"
  heroTitle="Kitchen Pantry<br /><em>Tiled to Perfection</em>"
  heroSub="Countertop and backsplash in one linear-foot rate ‚Äî perfectly aligned tiles, fully waterproofed joints, and a kitchen that looks as good as it performs."
  badge="Rs. 5,000 / lin.ft"
/>

<!-- Overview -->
<section class="overview">
  <div class="ov-text">
    <div class="stag">The Service</div>
    <h2>Countertop & Backsplash<br />in One Rate</h2>
    <p class="sdesc">
      Our kitchen pantry service covers the countertop surface and full-height
      backsplash behind it ‚Äî both measured and priced per linear foot of pantry
      length. One price, both surfaces, completely waterproof throughout.
    </p>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li>Countertop surface tiling ‚Äî full coverage with edge finishing</li>
      <li>Backsplash tiling from counter height to underside of upper cabinets</li>
      <li>Waterproof grout and silicone joint at counter-to-wall junction</li>
      <li>Perfectly aligned tile grid across both surfaces</li>
      <li>Neat cut-outs for electrical sockets and switches if required</li>
      <li>Swisstek stain-resistant grout throughout</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="ov-price reveal">
    <div class="price-card">
      <div class="pc-label">Per Linear Foot</div>
      <div class="pc-price">Rs. 5,000</div>
      <div class="pc-unit">countertop + backsplash</div>
      <div class="pc-note">Both surfaces covered in one rate. Measured along the length of the pantry counter.</div>
    </div>
    <p class="price-note">Labour only. Client supplies tiles.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- What's Covered -->
<section class="coverage">
  <div class="stag reveal">What's Covered</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Both Surfaces, One Price</h2>
  <p class="sdesc reveal">
    Measuring a kitchen pantry in linear feet means you get a simple, predictable
    price that covers the entire working surface area.
  </p>
  <div class="coverage-grid reveal">
    <div class="cov-card top">
      <div class="cov-icon">üî≤</div>
      <div class="cov-name">Countertop Surface</div>
      <div class="cov-desc">
        The full horizontal working surface ‚Äî tiled with your chosen stone, porcelain,
        or ceramic tile. Edge tiles are cut and finished flush or with a bull-nose tile.
        Completely waterproofed with silicone at the wall joint.
      </div>
      <div class="cov-dims">Typically 60‚Äì65 cm deep</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cov-card">
      <div class="cov-icon">üè†</div>
      <div class="cov-name">Backsplash</div>
      <div class="cov-desc">
        Vertical tiling behind the counter, from the counter edge up to the underside
        of your overhead cabinets (or to ceiling if there are no upper cabinets).
        Tile lines are continued from the countertop for visual consistency.
      </div>
      <div class="cov-dims">Typically 45‚Äì60 cm tall</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cov-card">
      <div class="cov-icon">üíß</div>
      <div class="cov-name">Waterproof Joints</div>
      <div class="cov-desc">
        The junction between countertop and backsplash is sealed with food-safe
        silicone rather than grout ‚Äî this flexible joint prevents water ingress and
        cracking as the structure moves.
      </div>
      <div class="cov-dims">Silicone bead, not grout</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cov-card">
      <div class="cov-icon">‚ö°</div>
      <div class="cov-name">Socket Cut-outs</div>
      <div class="cov-desc">
        Electrical sockets and switches in the backsplash area are carefully cut
        around ‚Äî tile cut to fit around the socket box, neat and precise, no cracking
        or chipping around the opening.
      </div>
      <div class="cov-dims">Included at no extra charge</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Tile Types -->
<section class="tile-types">
  <div class="stag reveal">Material Options</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Popular Tile Choices<br />for Kitchen Pantries</h2>
  <p class="sdesc reveal">
    We work with all tile materials commonly used in kitchens ‚Äî each has
    different handling requirements we account for in the installation.
  </p>
  <div class="types-grid reveal">
    <div class="type-card">
      <div class="type-name">Porcelain</div>
      <div class="type-stars">‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ</div>
      <div class="type-desc">Hardest and most stain-resistant option. Ideal for countertops under heavy use. Requires a diamond blade for cutting.</div>
      <div class="type-tags">
        <span>Heat Resistant</span><span>Stain Resistant</span><span>Low Maintenance</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="type-card featured">
      <div class="type-name">Large Format Stone-look</div>
      <div class="type-stars">‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ</div>
      <div class="type-desc">600√ó600 or 600√ó1200 porcelain tiles mimicking marble or granite ‚Äî fewer grout joints, contemporary look. Our most requested option.</div>
      <div class="type-tags">
        <span>Popular Choice</span><span>Modern Look</span><span>Easy Clean</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="type-card">
      <div class="type-name">Ceramic</div>
      <div class="type-stars">‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÜ</div>
      <div class="type-desc">Cost-effective, wide range of colours and patterns. Best suited for backsplash rather than countertop due to lower surface hardness.</div>
      <div class="type-tags">
        <span>Budget Friendly</span><span>Wide Range</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="type-card">
      <div class="type-name">Mosaic / Metro</div>
      <div class="type-stars">‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÜ‚òÜ</div>
      <div class="type-desc">Subway tiles and mosaics for the backsplash add character. More grout lines require regular maintenance to keep looking sharp.</div>
      <div class="type-tags">
        <span>Decorative</span><span>Classic Style</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Process -->
<section class="process">
  <div class="stag reveal">How We Work</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Installation Process</h2>
  <p class="sdesc reveal">Each kitchen is different ‚Äî we plan the tile layout before any cutting begins.</p>
  <div class="steps reveal">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">01</div>
      <div class="step-name">Measure & Plan</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Counter measured, tile layout planned to centre the pattern and minimise small cut pieces at visible ends.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">02</div>
      <div class="step-name">Surface Prep</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Counter substrate checked for level and soundness. Any high spots ground down, low spots filled with patching compound.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">03</div>
      <div class="step-name">Countertop Tiling</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Tiles set in adhesive from the front edge back ‚Äî front edge tile has a finished face (bull-nose or under-mounted edge tile).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">04</div>
      <div class="step-name">Backsplash Tiling</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Backsplash set from the counter level up ‚Äî tile courses aligned with the countertop joints for a continuous grid.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">05</div>
      <div class="step-name">Grouting</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Swisstek grout applied to all joints. Junction between counter and wall left open for silicone application.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">06</div>
      <div class="step-name">Silicone & Clean</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Silicone bead applied at counter-to-wall junction. Full clean-down, grout haze removed, surfaces polished.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq">
  <div class="stag reveal">FAQ</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Common Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list reveal">
    <details class="faq-item" open>
      <summary>How is the linear footage measured?</summary>
      <p>We measure along the front edge of your counter ‚Äî one linear foot covers the counter depth (typically 60 cm) plus the backsplash height (typically 45‚Äì60 cm). Complex L-shapes or island configurations are measured as total linear run.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can you tile over an existing tiled countertop?</summary>
      <p>In most cases yes, if the existing tiles are firmly bonded, flat, and there is headroom under overhead cabinets. We assess this during the free site visit.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What edge finish is used on the countertop front?</summary>
      <p>We can use a bull-nose tile (rounded edge), an under-mounted edge tile, or a mitred corner depending on your preference and the tile selected. We discuss this with you before cutting begins.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Is the area around the sink included?</summary>
      <p>Yes, the full countertop run is covered including around sink cut-outs. If you need a new sink hole cut in the tile, let us know in advance as this requires a diamond hole saw.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How soon can I use the kitchen after tiling?</summary>
      <p>Light use is possible after 24 hours. We recommend waiting 48 hours before placing heavy items on the counter and 72 hours before getting the surface wet.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .overview {
    background: var(--off-white);
    padding: 5.5rem 4rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .check-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: .7rem;
    margin-top: .5rem;
  }

  .check-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: .75rem;
    font-size: .9rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .check-list li::before {
    content: '‚óÜ';
    font-size: .42rem;
    color: var(--clay);
    margin-top: .4rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .price-card {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 2rem 2.2rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pc-label {
    font-size: .65rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .12em;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,.45);
    margin-bottom: .5rem;
  }

  .pc-price {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
